\begin_layout Standard
To introduce new agricultural technologies, some level of subsidy is often
 used.
 Private sector often use trail packs, as they realize farmers may be reluctant
 to try out a new product.
 Public actors may think commercial seed are out of reach of poor households
 and want to kick start adoption by providing the initial investment.
 The case for free (or subsidies) inputs also stems from potential externalities.
