\begin_layout Subsection
Fit risk
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fit risk is an important constraint to improved seed adoption and varietal
 turnover in many low and middle income countries.
 Fit risk emerges if a farmer is not unsure if a particularly new technology
 is suitable to their specific characteristics (eg will it grow on my land,
 will I like the taste of it).
 Fit risk is inherently idiosyncratic in nature.
 As such, little can be learned from social networks and experimenting on
 own plots is necessary.
 
\end_layout

